file=AI & Agents/scout/operational/tool/scout-tool-requirements.md · s—t:scout — Tool Requirements=**This file specifies needs; it does not grant them.** Access is configured at deployment (operator/platform; Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 apply).\n · tb=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| ecosystem-scanning \| web read access (scan sources — via the Shared OS web-search capability when built, PENDING) \| the sweep \| · tb=\| tool-evaluation-intake \| sandboxed trial environment (quinn's policy); file write (own reports) \| criteria-first trials \| · tb=\| adopt-reject-registry \| file read/write (own registry) \| verdict memory \| · tb=\| marketplace-skill-scouting \| web read access (marketplaces); file read (fleet PENDING notes) \| solicited searches \| · s—t:scout — Tool Requirements=Web search/browse is a cross-agent capability — it belongs to the Shared OS layer (PROJECT-HANDOFF §7), not baked in here (playbook §7 rule). scout is its heaviest consumer and the natural test case when that layer is built.\n